certified nurse midwives; to amend Section 34-21-93.1, Code of
SB110 INTRODUCED
29 Alabama 1975; to provide that an endorsement by a certified
30 registered nurse practitioner or certified nurse midwife on a
31 physical examination form for participation in school
32 athletics satisfies any requirement for the endorsement of a
33 physician on the required form; and to prohibit a public K-12
34 school from being a member of an athletic association that
35 does not accept physical examination forms for participation
36 in school athletics endorsed in compliance with this act.
37 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
38 Section 1. Section 34-21-93.1 of the Code of Alabama
39 1975, is amended to read as follows:
40 "§34-21-93.1
41 (a) When any law or rule requires a signature,
42 certification, stamp, verification, affidavit, or endorsement
43 by a physician, the document shall be deemed to authorize a
44 signature, certification, stamp, verification, affidavit, or
45 endorsement by a certified registered nurse practitioner or
46 certified nurse midwife for the items listed in this section.
47 The authority in this section for a certified registered nurse
48 practitioner and a certified nurse midwife shall be subject to
49 an active collaboration agreement. This section applies to all
50 of the following:
51 (1) Certification of disability for patients to receive
52 special access parking or disability access parking tags or
53 placards.
54 (2) A signature required for any of the following:
55 a. The following documents that require a complete
56 history and physical examination consistent with the examining
Page 2

history and physical examination consistent with the examining
