57 provider's scope of practice and certification:
58 1. Physicals for bus drivers in this state using State
59 of Alabama forms.
60 2. Physicals to verify eligibility for students to
61 participate in the Special Olympics.
62 3. Employment and pre-employment physicals for
63 Transportation Security Agency (TSA) employees at an airport
64 or for governmental employees such as firefighters and law
65 enforcement officers.
66 4. Adoptive parent applications.
67 5. College or trade school physicals.
68 6. Boy Scout or Girl Scout physicals or physical
69 required by similar organizations.
70 7. Physicals to verify eligibility for students to
71 participate in K-12 school athletic activities including, but
72 not limited to, interscholastic athletic activities.
73 b. Forms excusing a potential jury member due to an
74 illness.
75 c. Forms relating to absenteeism for employment or
76 school purposes, including, but not limited to, documents
77 associated with the federal Family and Medical Leave Act.
78 d. Authorizations for durable medical equipment.
79 e. Authorizations for diabetic testing supplies.
80 f. Authorization for diabetic shoes.
81 g. Home health recertification orders after initial
82 certification.
83 h. Within the state Medicaid system, any and all forms
84 for the ordering of medications, nutritional supplements, or
