85 infant formulas, or referrals to providers of medical
86 specialties, home health services, and physical or occupation
87 therapy.
88 i. Death certificates.
89 j. Forms, including physical examination forms, needed
90 for certifications in residential or inpatient dwellings
91 within the Department of Mental Health.
92 k. Forms for ambulance transport.
93 l. Forms for donor breast milk.
94 m. Required documentation allowing a diabetic to renew
95 or obtain a driver's license.
96 (b) Additional forms may be approved by rule under the
97 Alabama Administrative Procedure Act by the State Board of
98 Medical Examiners, after consulting with the state
99 professional society of nurse practitioners, the state
100 professional society of nurse midwives, the state professional
101 society of physicians, or the Joint Committee of the State
102 Board of Medical Examiners and the Board of Nursing for
103 Advanced Practice Nurses as established by Section 34-21-81,
104 whichever is appropriate.
105 (c) This section shall not be construed to expand the
106 scope of practice for any certified registered nurse
107 practitioner or certified nurse midwife.
108 (d) This section does not expand the scope of a
109 collaborative physician's responsibility with regard to nurse
110 practitioners or nurse midwives under the laws of this state.
111 (e) Any document signed or otherwise endorsed by a
112 certified registered nurse practitioner or certified nurse
